==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imbrown
<hw>Im*brown"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> in + <ets>brown</ets>. Cf. <er>Embrown</er>.]</ety>
<def>To make brown; to obscure; to darken; to tan; <as>as, features
<ex>imbrowned</ex> by exposure</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mountain mass by scorching skies <qex>imbrowned</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imbrue</ent>⟦br⟧
